cnatConfTable.name: cnatConfTable
cnatConfTable.description: This table specifies the configuration attributes for a device supporting NAT function.

cnatConfEntry.name: cnatConfEntry
cnatConfEntry.description: Each entry in the cnatConfTable holds a set of configuration parameters associated with an instance of NAT. Entries in the cnatConfTable are created and deleted using the cnatConfStatus object.

cnatConfName.name: cnatConfName
cnatConfName.description: The locally arbitrary, but unique identifier associated with this cnatConfEntry.

cnatConfServiceType.name: cnatConfServiceType
cnatConfServiceType.description: An indication of the direction in which new sessions are permitted and the extent of translation done within the IP and transport headers.

cnatConfTimeoutIcmpIdle.name: cnatConfTimeoutIcmpIdle
cnatConfTimeoutIcmpIdle.description: The interval of time for which an ICMP protocol session, associated with this configuration, is allowed to remain valid without any activity.

cnatConfTimeoutUdpIdle.name: cnatConfTimeoutUdpIdle
cnatConfTimeoutUdpIdle.description: The interval of time for which a UDP protocol session, associated with this configuration, is allowed to remain valid without any activity.

cnatConfTimeoutTcpIdle.name: cnatConfTimeoutTcpIdle
cnatConfTimeoutTcpIdle.description: The interval of time for which a TCP protocol session, associated with this configuration, is allowed to remain valid without any activity. This timeout value applies to a TCP session during its data transfer phase.

cnatConfTimeoutTcpNeg.name: cnatConfTimeoutTcpNeg
cnatConfTimeoutTcpNeg.description: The interval of time for which a TCP protocol session, associated with this configuration, is allowed to remain valid without any activity. This timeout value applies to a TCP session during its establishment and termination phases.

cnatConfTimeoutOther.name: cnatConfTimeoutOther
cnatConfTimeoutOther.description: The interval of time for which a protocol session other than ICMP, UDP and TCP, associated with this configuration, is allowed to remain valid, without any activity.

cnatConfMaxBindLeaseTime.name: cnatConfMaxBindLeaseTime
cnatConfMaxBindLeaseTime.description: The maximum lease time for the BIND, associated with this configuration. Unless the lease time is renewed, a BIND will not be valid past the lease time. As a special case, a value of 0 may be assumed to indicate no lease time limit. Typically, this attribute is of relevance only in conjunction with Realm-Specific-IP (RSIP) operation.

cnatConfMaxBindIdleTime.name: cnatConfMaxBindIdleTime
cnatConfMaxBindIdleTime.description: The maximum time, associated with this configuration, to allow a dynamic BIND to remain valid with no NAT session hanging off this BIND. By default for NATIVE NAT maximum Idle time is 0. External agents could control this parameter differently. Static Binds and lease time limited BINDs are not affected by this parameter.

cnatConfStorageType.name: cnatConfStorageType
cnatConfStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row.

cnatConfStatus.name: cnatConfStatus
cnatConfStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

cnatConfStaticAddrMapTable.name: cnatConfStaticAddrMapTable
cnatConfStaticAddrMapTable.description: This table lists configuration for static NAT entries. This table has an expansion dependent relationship on the cnatConfTable. When an SNMP entity deletes a conceptual row from the cnatConfTable, then the corresponding entries are deleted from cnatConfStaticAddrMapTable.

cnatConfStaticAddrMapEntry.name: cnatConfStaticAddrMapEntry
cnatConfStaticAddrMapEntry.description: A description of a static NAT entry. This entry contributes to the static NAT table of the device.

cnatConfStaticAddrMapName.name: cnatConfStaticAddrMapName
cnatConfStaticAddrMapName.description: An arbitrary, but unique identifier associated with this cnatConfStaticAddrMapEntry. The value of this object is unique across both the static address map and the dynamic address map tables.

cnatConfStaticAddrMapType.name: cnatConfStaticAddrMapType
cnatConfStaticAddrMapType.description: Address (and Transport-ID) maps may be defined for both inbound and outbound direction. Outbound address map refers to mapping a selected set of addresses from private realm to a selected set of addresses in external realm; whereas inbound address map refers to mapping a set of addresses from the external realm to private realm.

cnatConfStaticLocalAddrFrom.name: cnatConfStaticLocalAddrFrom
cnatConfStaticLocalAddrFrom.description: This object specifies the first IP address of the range of IP addresses mapped by this translation entry.

cnatConfStaticLocalAddrTo.name: cnatConfStaticLocalAddrTo
cnatConfStaticLocalAddrTo.description: This object specifies the last IP address of the range of IP addresses mapped by this translation entry. If only a single address being mapped, the value of this object is equal to the value of cnatConfStaticLocalAddrFrom. The number addresses in the range defined by cnatConfStaticLocalAddrFrom and cnatConfStaticLocalAddrTo should be equal to the number of addresses in the range defined by cnatConfStaticGlobalAddrFrom and cnatConfStaticGlobalAddrTo.

cnatConfStaticLocalPortFrom.name: cnatConfStaticLocalPortFrom
cnatConfStaticLocalPortFrom.description: If this conceptual row describes a basic NAT, then the value of this object is '0'. If this conceptual row describes NAPT, then the value of this object specifies the first port number in the range of ports being mapped. If the translation specifies a single port, then the value of this object is equal to the value of cnatConfStaticLocalPortTo.

cnatConfStaticLocalPortTo.name: cnatConfStaticLocalPortTo
cnatConfStaticLocalPortTo.description: If this conceptual row describes a basic NAT, then the value of this object is '0'. If this conceptual row describes NAPT, then the value of this object specifies the last port number in the range of ports being mapped. If the translation specifies a single port, then the value of this object is equal to the value of cnatConfStaticLocalPortFrom.

cnatConfStaticGlobalAddrFrom.name: cnatConfStaticGlobalAddrFrom
cnatConfStaticGlobalAddrFrom.description: This object specifies the first IP address of the range of IP addresses being mapped to.

cnatConfStaticGlobalAddrTo.name: cnatConfStaticGlobalAddrTo
cnatConfStaticGlobalAddrTo.description: This object specifies the last IP address of the range of IP addresses being mapped to. If only a single address is being mapped to, the value of this object is equal to the value of cnatConfStaticGlobalAddrFrom.The number addresses in the range defined by cnatConfStaticGlobalAddrFrom and cnatConfStaticGlobalAddrTo should be equal to the number of addresses in the range defined by cnatConfStaticLocalAddrFrom and cnatConfStaticLocalAddrTo.

cnatConfStaticGlobalPortFrom.name: cnatConfStaticGlobalPortFrom
cnatConfStaticGlobalPortFrom.description: If this conceptual row describes a basic NAT, then the value of this object is '0'. If this conceptual row describes NAPT, then the value of this object specifies the first port number in the range of ports being mapped to. If the translation specifies a single port, then the value of this object is equal to the value cnatConfStaticGlobalPortTo.

cnatConfStaticGlobalPortTo.name: cnatConfStaticGlobalPortTo
cnatConfStaticGlobalPortTo.description: If this conceptual row describes a basic NAT, then the value of this object is '0'. If this conceptual describes NAPT, then the value of this object specifies the last port number in the range of ports being to. If the translation specifies a single port, then the value of this object is equal to the value of cnatConfStaticGlobalPortFrom.

cnatConfStaticProtocol.name: cnatConfStaticProtocol
cnatConfStaticProtocol.description: This object specifies a protocol identifier. If the value of this object is '0', then this basic NAT entry applies to all IP traffic. If the value of this object is non-zero, then this NAT entry only applies to IP traffic with the specified protocol.

cnatConfStaticAddrMapStorageType.name: cnatConfStaticAddrMapStorageType
cnatConfStaticAddrMapStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row.

cnatConfStaticAddrMapStatus.name: cnatConfStaticAddrMapStatus
cnatConfStaticAddrMapStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to either createAndGo(4) or createAndWait(5).

cnatConfDynAddrMapTable.name: cnatConfDynAddrMapTable
cnatConfDynAddrMapTable.description: This table lists dynamic NAT entries. This table has an expansion dependent relationship on the cnatConfTable. When an SNMP entity deletes a conceptual row from the cnatConfTable, then the corresponding entries are deleted from cnatConfDynAddrMapTable.

cnatConfDynAddrMapEntry.name: cnatConfDynAddrMapEntry
cnatConfDynAddrMapEntry.description: A description of a dynamic NAT entry. This entry contributes to the dynamic NAT table of the device.

cnatConfDynAddrMapName.name: cnatConfDynAddrMapName
cnatConfDynAddrMapName.description: An arbitrary, but unique identifier associated with this cnatConfDynAddrMapEntry. The value of this object is unique across both the static address map and the dynamic address map tables.

cnatConfDynAddressMapType.name: cnatConfDynAddressMapType
cnatConfDynAddressMapType.description: Address (and Transport-ID) maps may be defined for both inbound and outbound direction. Outbound address map refers to mapping a selected set of addresses from private realm to a selected set of addresses in external realm; whereas inbound address map refers to mapping a set of addresses from the external realm to private realm.

cnatConfDynLocalAddrFrom.name: cnatConfDynLocalAddrFrom
cnatConfDynLocalAddrFrom.description: This object specifies the first IP address of the range of IP addresses mapped by this translation entry.

cnatConfDynLocalAddrTo.name: cnatConfDynLocalAddrTo
cnatConfDynLocalAddrTo.description: This object specifies the last IP address of the range of IP addresses mapped by this translation entry.

cnatConfDynLocalPortFrom.name: cnatConfDynLocalPortFrom
cnatConfDynLocalPortFrom.description: If this conceptual row describes a basic NAT, then the value of this object is '0'. If this conceptual row describes NAPT, then the value of this object specifies the first port number in the range of ports being mapped. If the translation specifies a single port, then the value of this object is equal to the value of cnatConfDynLocalPortTo.

cnatConfDynLocalPortTo.name: cnatConfDynLocalPortTo
cnatConfDynLocalPortTo.description: If this conceptual row describes a basic NAT, then the value of this object is '0'. If this conceptual row describes NAPT, then the value of this object specifies the last port number in the range of ports being mapped. If the translation specifies a single port, then the value of this object is equal to the value of cnatConfDynLocalPortFrom.

cnatConfDynGlobalAddrFrom.name: cnatConfDynGlobalAddrFrom
cnatConfDynGlobalAddrFrom.description: This object specifies the first IP address of the range of IP addresses being mapped to.

cnatConfDynGlobalAddrTo.name: cnatConfDynGlobalAddrTo
cnatConfDynGlobalAddrTo.description: This object specifies the last IP address of the range of IP addresses being mapped to.

cnatConfDynGlobalPortFrom.name: cnatConfDynGlobalPortFrom
cnatConfDynGlobalPortFrom.description: If this conceptual row describes a basic NAT, then the value of this object is '0'. If this conceptual row describes NAPT, then the value of this object specifies the first port number in the range of ports being mapped to. If the translation specifies a single port, then the value of this object is equal to the value of cnatConfDynGlobalPortTo.

cnatConfDynGlobalPortTo.name: cnatConfDynGlobalPortTo
cnatConfDynGlobalPortTo.description: If this conceptual row describes a basic NAT, then the value of this object is '0'. If this conceptual row describes NAPT, then the value of this object specifies the last port number in the range of ports being mapped to. If the translation specifies a single port, then the value of this object is equal to the value of cnatConfDynGlobalPortFrom.

cnatConfDynProtocol.name: cnatConfDynProtocol
cnatConfDynProtocol.description: This object specifies a protocol identifier. If the value of this object is '0', then this basic NAT entry applies to all IP traffic. If the value of this object is non-zero, then this NAT entry only applies to IP traffic with the specified protocol.

cnatConfDynAddrMapStorageType.name: cnatConfDynAddrMapStorageType
cnatConfDynAddrMapStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row.

cnatConfDynAddrMapStatus.name: cnatConfDynAddrMapStatus
cnatConfDynAddrMapStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to either createAndGo(4) or createAndWait(5).

cnatInterfaceTable.name: cnatInterfaceTable
cnatInterfaceTable.description: This table holds information regarding the interface on which NAT is enabled.

cnatInterfaceEntry.name: cnatInterfaceEntry
cnatInterfaceEntry.description: Each entry in the NAT Interface Table holds information regarding an interface on which NAT is enabled.

cnatInterfaceIndex.name: cnatInterfaceIndex
cnatInterfaceIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface on which NAT is enabled.

cnatInterfaceRealm.name: cnatInterfaceRealm
cnatInterfaceRealm.description: This object identifies whether this interface is connected to the private or the public realm.

cnatInterfaceStorageType.name: cnatInterfaceStorageType
cnatInterfaceStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row.

cnatInterfaceStatus.name: cnatInterfaceStatus
cnatInterfaceStatus.description: Status of NAT on this interface. An active status indicates that NAT is enabled on this interface.

cnatAddrBindNumberOfEntries.name: cnatAddrBindNumberOfEntries
cnatAddrBindNumberOfEntries.description: This object maintains a count of the number of entries that currently exist in the cnatAddrBindTable.

cnatAddrBindTable.name: cnatAddrBindTable
cnatAddrBindTable.description: This table holds information about the currently active NAT BINDs.

cnatAddrBindEntry.name: cnatAddrBindEntry
cnatAddrBindEntry.description: Each entry in the NAT BIND table holds information about a NAT BIND that is currently active.

cnatAddrBindLocalAddr.name: cnatAddrBindLocalAddr
cnatAddrBindLocalAddr.description: This object represents the private-realm specific network layer address, which maps to the public-realm address represented by cnatAddrBindGlobalAddr.

cnatAddrBindGlobalAddr.name: cnatAddrBindGlobalAddr
cnatAddrBindGlobalAddr.description: This object represents the public-realm network layer address that maps to the private-realm network layer address represented by cnatAddrBindLocalAddr.

cnatAddrBindId.name: cnatAddrBindId
cnatAddrBindId.description: This object represents a BIND id that is dynamically assigned to each BIND by a NAT enabled device. Each BIND is represented by a unique BIND id across both, the Address bind and Address-Port bind tables.

cnatAddrBindDirection.name: cnatAddrBindDirection
cnatAddrBindDirection.description: This object represents the direction of the BIND. A BIND may be either uni-directional or bi-directional, same as the orientation of the address map, based on which this bind is formed. The direction of this bind is with reference to the private realm.

cnatAddrBindType.name: cnatAddrBindType
cnatAddrBindType.description: This object indicates whether the BIND is static or dynamic.

cnatAddrBindConfName.name: cnatAddrBindConfName
cnatAddrBindConfName.description: This object is a pointer to the cnatConfTable entry (and the parameters of that entry) which was used in creating this BIND.

cnatAddrBindSessionCount.name: cnatAddrBindSessionCount
cnatAddrBindSessionCount.description: Number of sessions currently using this BIND.

cnatAddrBindCurrentIdleTime.name: cnatAddrBindCurrentIdleTime
cnatAddrBindCurrentIdleTime.description: At any given instance of time, this object indicates the time that this BIND has been idle with no sessions attached to it. The value represented by this object is of relevance only when the value of Maximum Idle time (cnatConfMaxBindIdleTime) is non-zero.

cnatAddrBindInTranslate.name: cnatAddrBindInTranslate
cnatAddrBindInTranslate.description: The number of inbound packets that were translated as per this BIND entry.

cnatAddrBindOutTranslate.name: cnatAddrBindOutTranslate
cnatAddrBindOutTranslate.description: The number of outbound packets that were translated as per this BIND entry.

cnatAddrPortBindNumberOfEntries.name: cnatAddrPortBindNumberOfEntries
cnatAddrPortBindNumberOfEntries.description: This object maintains a count of the number of entries that currently exist in the cnatAddrPortBindTable.

cnatAddrPortBindTable.name: cnatAddrPortBindTable
cnatAddrPortBindTable.description: This table holds information about the currently active NAPT BINDs.

cnatAddrPortBindEntry.name: cnatAddrPortBindEntry
cnatAddrPortBindEntry.description: Each entry in the this table holds information a NAPT BIND that is currently active.

cnatAddrPortBindLocalAddr.name: cnatAddrPortBindLocalAddr
cnatAddrPortBindLocalAddr.description: This object represents the private-realm specific network layer address which, in conjunction with cnatAddrPortBindLocalPort, maps to the public-realm network layer address and transport id represented by cnatAddrPortBindGlobalAddr and cnatAddrPortBindGlobalPort respectively.

cnatAddrPortBindLocalPort.name: cnatAddrPortBindLocalPort
cnatAddrPortBindLocalPort.description: This object represents the private-realm specific port number (or query ID in case of ICMP messages) which, in conjunction with cnatAddrPortBindLocalAddr, maps to the public-realm network layer address and transport id represented by cnatAddrPortBindGlobalAddr and cnatAddrPortBindGlobalPort respectively.

cnatAddrPortBindProtocol.name: cnatAddrPortBindProtocol
cnatAddrPortBindProtocol.description: This object specifies a protocol identifier. If the value of this object is '0', then this BIND entry applies to all IP traffic. If the value of this object is non-zero, then this NAT entry only applies to IP traffic with the specified protocol.

cnatAddrPortBindGlobalAddr.name: cnatAddrPortBindGlobalAddr
cnatAddrPortBindGlobalAddr.description: This object represents the public-realm specific network layer address that, in conjunction with cnatAddrPortBindGlobalPort, maps to the private-realm network layer address and transport id represented by cnatAddrPortBindLocalAddr and cnatAddrPortBindLocalPort respectively.

cnatAddrPortBindGlobalPort.name: cnatAddrPortBindGlobalPort
cnatAddrPortBindGlobalPort.description: This object represents the port number (or query id in case of ICMP) that, in conjunction with cnatAddrPortBindGlobalAddr, maps to the private-realm network layer address and transport id represented by cnatAddrPortBindLocalAddr and cnatAddrPortBindLocalPort respectively.

cnatAddrPortBindId.name: cnatAddrPortBindId
cnatAddrPortBindId.description: This object represents a BIND id that is dynamically assigned to each BIND by a NAT enabled device. Each BIND is represented by a unique BIND id across both, the Address Bind and Address-Port Bind tables.

cnatAddrPortBindDirection.name: cnatAddrPortBindDirection
cnatAddrPortBindDirection.description: This object represents the direction of the BIND. A BIND may be either uni-directional or bi-directional, same as the orientation of the address map, based on which this bind is formed. The direction of this bind is with reference to the private realm.

cnatAddrPortBindType.name: cnatAddrPortBindType
cnatAddrPortBindType.description: This object indicates whether the BIND is static or dynamic.

cnatAddrPortBindConfName.name: cnatAddrPortBindConfName
cnatAddrPortBindConfName.description: This object is a pointer to the cnatConfTable entry (and the parameters of that entry) which was used in creating this BIND.

cnatAddrPortBindSessionCount.name: cnatAddrPortBindSessionCount
cnatAddrPortBindSessionCount.description: Number of sessions currently using this BIND.

cnatAddrPortBindCurrentIdleTime.name: cnatAddrPortBindCurrentIdleTime
cnatAddrPortBindCurrentIdleTime.description: At any given instance of time, this object indicates the time that this BIND has been idle with no sessions attached to it. The value represented by this object is of relevance only when the value of Maximum Idle time (cnatConfMaxBindIdleTime) is non-zero.

cnatAddrPortBindInTranslate.name: cnatAddrPortBindInTranslate
cnatAddrPortBindInTranslate.description: The number of inbound packets that were translated as per this BIND entry.

cnatAddrPortBindOutTranslate.name: cnatAddrPortBindOutTranslate
cnatAddrPortBindOutTranslate.description: The number of outbound packets that were translated as per this BIND entry.

cnatSessionTable.name: cnatSessionTable
cnatSessionTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing one entry for each NAT session currently active on this NAT device.

cnatSessionEntry.name: cnatSessionEntry
cnatSessionEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing information about an active NAT session on this NAT device.

cnatSessionBindId.name: cnatSessionBindId
cnatSessionBindId.description: This object represents a BIND id that is dynamically assigned to each BIND by a NAT enabled device. This bind id is that same as represented by the BindId objects in the Address bind and Address-Port bind tables.

cnatSessionId.name: cnatSessionId
cnatSessionId.description: The session ID for this NAT session.

cnatSessionDirection.name: cnatSessionDirection
cnatSessionDirection.description: The direction of this session with respect to the local network. 'inbound' indicates that this session was initiated from the public network into the private network. 'outbound' indicates that this session was initiated from the private network into the public network.

cnatSessionUpTime.name: cnatSessionUpTime
cnatSessionUpTime.description: The up time of this session in one-hundredths of a second.

cnatSessionProtocolType.name: cnatSessionProtocolType
cnatSessionProtocolType.description: The protocol type of this session. TCP and UDP sessions are uniquely identified by the tuple of (source IP address, source UDP/TCP port, destination IP address, destination TCP/UCP port). ICMP query sessions are identified by the tuple of (source IP address, ICMP query ID, destination IP address).

cnatSessionOrigPrivateAddr.name: cnatSessionOrigPrivateAddr
cnatSessionOrigPrivateAddr.description: The original IP address of the session endpoint that lies in the private network.

cnatSessionTransPrivateAddr.name: cnatSessionTransPrivateAddr
cnatSessionTransPrivateAddr.description: The translated IP address of the session endpoint that lies in the private network. The value of this object is equal to that of the original public IP Address (cnatSessionOrigPrivateAddr) when there is no translation.

cnatSessionOrigPrivatePort.name: cnatSessionOrigPrivatePort
cnatSessionOrigPrivatePort.description: The original transport port of the session endpoint that belongs to the private network. If this is an ICMP session then the value is the ICMP request ID.

cnatSessionTransPrivatePort.name: cnatSessionTransPrivatePort
cnatSessionTransPrivatePort.description: The translated transport port of the session that lies in the private network. The value of this object is equal to that of the original transport port (cnatSessionOrigPrivatePort) when there is no translation.

cnatSessionOrigPublicAddr.name: cnatSessionOrigPublicAddr
cnatSessionOrigPublicAddr.description: The original IP address of the session endpoint that lies in the public network.

cnatSessionTransPublicAddr.name: cnatSessionTransPublicAddr
cnatSessionTransPublicAddr.description: The translated IP address of the session endpoint that belongs to the public network. The value of this object is equal to that of the original public IP Address (cnatSessionOrigPublicAddr) when there is no translation.

cnatSessionOrigPublicPort.name: cnatSessionOrigPublicPort
cnatSessionOrigPublicPort.description: The original transport port of the session endpoint that belongs to the public network. If this is an ICMP session then the value contains the ICMP request ID.

cnatSessionTransPublicPort.name: cnatSessionTransPublicPort
cnatSessionTransPublicPort.description: The translated transport port of the session endpoint that belongs to the public network. The value of this object is equal to that of the original transport port (cnatSessionOrigPublicPort) when there is no translation.

cnatSessionCurrentIdletime.name: cnatSessionCurrentIdletime
cnatSessionCurrentIdletime.description: The time in one-hundredths of a second since a packet belonging to this session was last detected.

cnatSessionSecondBindId.name: cnatSessionSecondBindId
cnatSessionSecondBindId.description: The natBindId of the 'other' NAT binding incase of Twice NAT. An instance of this object contains a valid value only if the binding type for this session is TwiceNAT.

cnatSessionInTranslate.name: cnatSessionInTranslate
cnatSessionInTranslate.description: The number of inbound packets that were translated by this session.

cnatSessionOutTranslate.name: cnatSessionOutTranslate
cnatSessionOutTranslate.description: The number of outbound packets that were translated by this session.

cnatProtocolStatsTable.name: cnatProtocolStatsTable
cnatProtocolStatsTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing per protocol NAT statistics.

cnatProtocolStatsEntry.name: cnatProtocolStatsEntry
cnatProtocolStatsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing NAT statistics pertaining to a particular protocol.

cnatProtocolStatsName.name: cnatProtocolStatsName
cnatProtocolStatsName.description: This object represents the protocol pertaining to which statistics are reported.

cnatProtocolStatsInTranslate.name: cnatProtocolStatsInTranslate
cnatProtocolStatsInTranslate.description: The number of inbound packets, pertaining to the protocol identified by cnatProtocolStatsName, that underwent NAT.

cnatProtocolStatsOutTranslate.name: cnatProtocolStatsOutTranslate
cnatProtocolStatsOutTranslate.description: The number of outbound packets, pertaining to the protocol identified by cnatProtocolStatsName, that underwent NAT.

cnatProtocolStatsRejectCount.name: cnatProtocolStatsRejectCount
cnatProtocolStatsRejectCount.description: The number of packets, pertaining to the protocol identified by cnatProtocolStatsName, that had to be rejected/dropped due to lack of resources. These rejections could be due to session timeout, resource unavailability etc.

cnatAddrMapStatsTable.name: cnatAddrMapStatsTable
cnatAddrMapStatsTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing per address map NAT statistics.

cnatAddrMapStatsEntry.name: cnatAddrMapStatsEntry
cnatAddrMapStatsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing NAT statistics per address map.

cnatAddrMapStatsConfName.name: cnatAddrMapStatsConfName
cnatAddrMapStatsConfName.description: The name of the configuration (from the cnatConfTable), regarding which statistics are being reported. The configuration name along with Map name uniquely identifies an entry across both (static and dynamic) Address Map tables.

cnatAddrMapStatsMapName.name: cnatAddrMapStatsMapName
cnatAddrMapStatsMapName.description: The name of the Address Map (from the cnatConfStaticAddrMapTable/cnatConfDynAddrMapTable), regarding which statistics are being reported. The configuration name along with Map name uniquely identifies an entry across both (static and dynamic) Address Map tables.

cnatAddrMapStatsInTranslate.name: cnatAddrMapStatsInTranslate
cnatAddrMapStatsInTranslate.description: The number of inbound packets, pertaining to this address map entry, that were translated.

cnatAddrMapStatsOutTranslate.name: cnatAddrMapStatsOutTranslate
cnatAddrMapStatsOutTranslate.description: The number of outbound packets, pertaining to this address map entry, that were translated.

cnatAddrMapStatsNoResource.name: cnatAddrMapStatsNoResource
cnatAddrMapStatsNoResource.description: The number of packets, pertaining to this address map entry, that were dropped due to lack of addresses in the address pool identified by this address map. The value of this object should always be zero in case of static address map.

cnatAddrMapStatsAddrUsed.name: cnatAddrMapStatsAddrUsed
cnatAddrMapStatsAddrUsed.description: The number of addresses, pertaining to this address map, that are currently being used from the nat pool. The value of this object is irrelevant if the address map in question is a static address map.

cnatInterfaceStatsTable.name: cnatInterfaceStatsTable
cnatInterfaceStatsTable.description: This table augments the cnatInterfaceTable and provides statistics information pertaining to the specified interface.

cnatInterfaceStatsEntry.name: cnatInterfaceStatsEntry
cnatInterfaceStatsEntry.description: Each entry of the cnatInterfaceStatsTable represents stats pertaining to one interface, which is identified by its ifIndex.

cnatInterfacePktsIn.name: cnatInterfacePktsIn
cnatInterfacePktsIn.description: Number of packets received on this interface that were translated.

cnatInterfacePktsOut.name: cnatInterfacePktsOut
cnatInterfacePktsOut.description: Number of translated packets that were sent out this interface.
